As a financial teacher, my task is to evaluate the different solutions proposed by students for the financial calculation problem.
I will assess each solution based on the provided evaluation criteria, which include the Utilization of Provided Information,
Formula Accuracy, and Alignment with the Question.
In scoring, I will pay close attention to how each solution performs against these standards and provide corresponding reasons.
The scoring must be objective and fair, with appropriate deductions for minor errors while also recognizing the unique aspects of each solution.
Let's examine these solutions and provide my scores and justifications.